HEADWORD: Engulf
<hw>En*gulf"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Engulfed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Engulfing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>en-</ets>
+ <ets>gulf</ets>: cf. OF. <ets>engolfer</ets>. Cf.
<er>Ingulf</er>.]</ety> <def>To absorb or swallow up as in a
gulf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It quite <qex>engulfs</qex> all human thought.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Absorb</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

